Set 10
The source code for the AbstractGrid is in Appendix D.

1.Where is the is Valid method specified? Which classes provide an implementation of this	method?
Answer:
The is Valid method is specified in Grid. The class BoundedGrid and class UnboundedGrid gave implementation for this method.

2.Which AbstractGrid methods call this isValid method? Why dont the other need to call it?
Answer:
In getValidAdjacentLocation()
Because other using getValidAdjacentLocation() that to implement the code.

3.Which methods of the Grid interface are called in the getNeighbors method? Which classes provide implementations of these methods?
Answer:
getOccupiedAdjacentLocations(Location loc) & ArrayList<Object> add() method & get()

class abstractGrid() BoundedGrid() provide implementations of getOccupiedAdjacentLocation(Location loc)
class ArrayList provides implementations of add()
BoundedGrid() & UnboundedGrid() provide implementations of get()

4. Why must the get method which returns an object of tyoe E, be used in the getEmptyLocations method when this method returns locations, not objects of type E?
Answer:
It just use the get method to get is there an object on the location, if no, then add the location into the object.

5.What would be the effect of replacing the constant Location. HALF_RIGHT with Location RIGHT in the two places where it occurs in the getValidAdjacentLocations method?
Answer:
Then it just get 4 directions no 8 directions. NORTH EAST SOUTH WEST


